HEADWORD: Pleasance
<hw>Pleas"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>plaisance</ets>. See <er>Please</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Pleasure; merriment; gayety; delight; kindness.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark> <au>Shak.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Full great
<xex>pleasance</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Chaucer.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧A realm of
<xex>pleasance</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Tennyson.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A secluded part of a garden.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>pleasances</qex> of old Elizabethan houses.</q>
<rj><qau>Ruskin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

